WEBVTT

00:34.826 --> 00:36.203
You got to sit up.

00:39.414 --> 00:40.832
So when did this start?

00:40.916 --> 00:43.377
- Just as I pulled...
- Just as you pulled through the gate?

00:44.211 --> 00:45.587
I ain't never been to jail!

00:45.671 --> 00:47.548
I don't like this!

00:47.631 --> 00:48.715
Lean your head back.

00:50.133 --> 00:52.094
You can pass out if you want to.

00:52.177 --> 00:54.555
It ain't going to make a difference,
she'll still be in jail.

01:03.814 --> 01:05.983
Turn around,
put your back on the board.

01:06.066 --> 01:06.984
Look in camera one.

01:10.404 --> 01:11.321
Oh man...

01:11.405 --> 01:14.992
When I first walked through those doors,
I was scared.

01:15.742 --> 01:18.662
<i>It seems like you're in
some third world shithole.</i>

01:20.122 --> 01:24.501
You know what you get from being in jail?
You turn cold. You turn into an animal.

01:24.585 --> 01:27.796
Please let me go home.
Please, I want to go to my son.

01:29.214 --> 01:31.258
Bitch, I'm about to get out!

01:33.260 --> 01:35.345
I've been counting down for days now.

01:36.471 --> 01:38.056
<i>Walking out of here,</i>

01:38.181 --> 01:40.183
<i>it's the best feeling in the world.</i>

01:40.267 --> 01:42.436
- Take care of yourself and do good.
- I will, baby.

01:43.687 --> 01:46.648
<i>You walk out that front door
and you don't turn back.</i>

01:47.024 --> 01:48.483
<i>You just put it behind you.</i>

01:49.109 --> 01:51.820
<i>Never thought this fucking moment
would fucking happen!</i>

01:51.903 --> 01:54.031
<i>Being incarcerated,
it changes you.</i>

01:54.114 --> 01:58.368
<i>Just have a complete 360.
Your whole view of the world changes.</i>

02:33.028 --> 02:35.656
- Alexander, you been here before?
- No, ma'am.

02:35.739 --> 02:37.991
Look straight ahead for me. Face the U.

02:39.242 --> 02:40.994
What does it say above your eye?

02:41.078 --> 02:43.121
My mom's name. LaShonda.

02:43.664 --> 02:47.793
Here's your ID until you get a wristband.
When they do a count, pull this paper out.

02:47.876 --> 02:49.503
Go around the other side

02:51.630 --> 02:52.506
To your right.

02:57.135 --> 03:00.222
Bullshit! Damn!

03:08.021 --> 03:09.398
<i>What am I going to do?</i>

03:10.023 --> 03:12.484
<i>That's my first thought.
What am I going to do?</i>

03:14.319 --> 03:18.073
<i>You know, it's not good no matter
even if it's my first offense or what.</i>

03:18.699 --> 03:21.910
Just looks really bad.
You got a car full of three black people.

03:21.993 --> 03:27.207
Two weapons, all the drugs, all the
everything. Like, it just don't look good.

03:29.334 --> 03:32.087
I was just going to get my hair done
and come home.

03:33.714 --> 03:35.841
<i>Dontrell, he picked me up to my house,
you know.</i>

03:36.299 --> 03:38.552
I was going to his house,
his wife does hair.

03:38.677 --> 03:40.929
I was just going to get my dreads
redone, or something.

03:41.012 --> 03:43.598
But he said he had to pick up
one of his friends real quick,

03:43.682 --> 03:45.976
the other guy with the small hair.

03:46.518 --> 03:49.563
I wasn't thinking nothing. Got into the
car, take me to get a money order.

03:49.646 --> 03:51.398
I live right up the street
from the store.

03:51.940 --> 03:56.862
Um, we got pulled over for my tint
on the car being too dark.

03:56.945 --> 04:00.657
When they started searching the car
thoroughly and they found a bookbag,

04:00.741 --> 04:03.785
and they just start pulling
all this... all this shit out.

04:03.869 --> 04:06.455
And they found guns and drugs
in the vehicle.

04:07.247 --> 04:11.251
And they charged everybody. I know
nothing wasn't mine. So I'm not guilty.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.586
I'm completely innocent.

04:12.669 --> 04:14.171
You've got an innocent man
sitting here.

04:14.796 --> 04:17.507
Even though I'm innocent,
it's going to be hard.

04:22.012 --> 04:23.263
Yeah, bro, listen.

04:23.346 --> 04:26.767
The only thing we got a chance
of now is going to court.

04:26.850 --> 04:29.478
I'm just letting you know
what's going on, bro.

04:30.645 --> 04:31.980
Trell, I've been here before.

04:33.315 --> 04:35.150
I already know what goes on in Gwinnett.

04:35.233 --> 04:36.067
You know what I'm saying?

04:46.828 --> 04:49.748
The Gwinnett County Jail is located
in Gwinnett County, Georgia.

04:50.916 --> 04:54.044
That's just outside the city limits
of Lawrenceville,

04:54.127 --> 04:57.214
which is approximately 30 miles north
of the city of Atlanta.

05:01.218 --> 05:03.887
The jail right here is one
of the largest in the country.

05:05.138 --> 05:09.226
The size of this facility is roughly
just under a million square feet.

05:09.726 --> 05:12.312
You could take
20 full size football fields

05:12.395 --> 05:14.564
and put them inside
the square footage of this place.

05:18.819 --> 05:22.280
This facility is classified
as a pre-trial detention center.

05:23.865 --> 05:25.158
In the course of a year,

05:25.242 --> 05:28.453
35 to 37,000 inmates
come through these doors.

05:29.329 --> 05:30.789
It's a massive operation.

05:40.382 --> 05:44.386
<i>All right, ladies, there's
going to be free time at this time.</i>

05:45.220 --> 05:47.597
<i>You have free time at this time, ladies.</i>

05:51.017 --> 05:53.270
<i>Been here 78 days.
Tomorrow will be 79.</i>

05:54.646 --> 05:56.189
<i>I've been here six times.</i>

05:57.440 --> 05:59.776
<i>I don't wanna be here no more.
That's for sure.</i>

06:00.861 --> 06:03.780
<i>It's hard, but at the same time
it actually helped me.</i>

06:03.864 --> 06:06.575
If I was out on the streets, honestly,
I'd probably be dead right now.

06:13.999 --> 06:17.460
<i>I don't have a license. Abuses of drugs
actually took them from me.</i>

06:17.544 --> 06:21.006
<i>I drove more than once
on a suspended license,</i>

06:21.089 --> 06:24.009
<i>and I'm a habitual violator
which caused me to be a felony.</i>

06:27.345 --> 06:29.556
I'm really nervous and scared to go home.

06:29.639 --> 06:30.473
Why?

06:31.892 --> 06:32.726
I don't know.

06:34.227 --> 06:35.103
I know I miss my mama.

06:35.186 --> 06:37.230
I haven't been home in so long!

06:37.314 --> 06:41.026
Well, it's new, you know?
Actually, I'm going home... this time.

06:41.109 --> 06:43.737
Not on the streets, not homeless.
I'm going home.

06:43.820 --> 06:44.946
Home. To a real home.

06:45.030 --> 06:45.947
That'll be great.

06:46.031 --> 06:47.574
Like somebody
that actually cares, you know?

06:47.657 --> 06:48.491
Yeah.

06:48.575 --> 06:49.993
Haven't had that in a long time.

06:50.076 --> 06:51.244
I'm happy for you.

06:51.745 --> 06:53.997
I'm trying to figure out
how I've lost everything.

06:55.040 --> 06:58.501
<i>My family say I chose men and drugs
over them, which is true.</i>

07:01.838 --> 07:03.590
<i>My mama's been clean for 27 years.</i>

07:03.673 --> 07:05.675
<i>I asked if I could come stay
with her when I get out.</i>

07:06.301 --> 07:07.469
<i>She said that would be great.</i>

07:07.552 --> 07:10.805
She would like to start over because
she's missed all the years in my life.

07:10.889 --> 07:12.557
And now she's trying to make up for it.

07:15.727 --> 07:19.731
I'm going to have the great experience of
being able to experience my family again.

07:20.315 --> 07:22.651
<i>And now they're actually trying
to help me...</i>

07:23.109 --> 07:26.404
<i>you know, have a normal life again,
which is going to be hard.</i>

07:26.488 --> 07:28.073
<i>It's going to be a struggle for real.</i>

07:30.450 --> 07:32.077
Struggle, Struggleville.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.372
I'm nervous. I'm scared to go home.

07:36.373 --> 07:39.376
You know, I'm scared
that I'm going to fuck up again.

07:48.885 --> 07:50.470
Mr. Russom, if you'll come out, sir.

07:52.430 --> 07:55.266
Mr. Russom, come on down.
Stand in that yellow square.

08:06.027 --> 08:09.072
Why are you messing around with this
stuff? You're too young for all this mess.

08:09.155 --> 08:10.865
I was in the wrong place
at the wrong time.

08:10.949 --> 08:12.492
- Is that what it was?
- Yes, ma'am.

08:12.575 --> 08:15.537
I hope that that's the case.
You're too young to be in all this mess.

08:15.620 --> 08:17.998
You need to be in school,
getting you an education.

08:19.040 --> 08:20.333
Doing good for this world.

08:20.500 --> 08:23.420
- I'm going to college next month.
- Are you? Okay!

08:25.422 --> 08:27.632
All right, you've got two felony charges.

08:28.591 --> 08:31.761
Possession with intent to distribute
marijuana is one of them.

08:31.845 --> 08:34.847
The other one is possession of a gun.
What you got a gun for?

08:34.931 --> 08:37.558
- Wrong place, wrong time.
- I know, wrong place, wrong time.

08:43.940 --> 08:46.568
$11,400 is your total bond.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.322
In order to bond out, you can pay cash.

08:51.740 --> 08:53.366
That would be the entire amount.

08:53.450 --> 08:57.579
You can go through a bonding company.
Bonding companies charge 12 to 15 percent.

08:57.662 --> 09:00.665
Uh, what would be
12 to 15 percent of this?

09:04.711 --> 09:08.798
$1,710 is 15 percent.
So that's the high side.

09:08.882 --> 09:12.385
So, you're looking at about $1,700
or less at a bonding company.

09:12.469 --> 09:15.263
- Okay? Any other questions?
- Uh, no, ma'am.

09:23.605 --> 09:25.315
What they do with lil' bro?

09:25.690 --> 09:28.234
They're keeping him separated
for some reason, bro.

09:30.403 --> 09:31.988
Somebody's gonna have to
take the charge, bro,

09:32.072 --> 09:33.948
when they're charging all three of us
for the same shit!

09:35.450 --> 09:38.536
Only thing I'm thinking about right now
is my fucking kid, man.

09:39.537 --> 09:41.581
Well, my girl's tired of this shit, bro.

09:41.664 --> 09:43.291
He ain't got none of that going, do he?

09:44.626 --> 09:46.586
I got a lot to fucking lose, bro.

09:47.253 --> 09:50.465
- I'm not going down for no case.
- So what you want him to do?

09:51.049 --> 09:52.425
He gotta 'fess up.

09:52.509 --> 09:55.095
On his first fucking charge.

09:55.512 --> 09:57.305
Don't forget you're on the mic.

09:57.680 --> 09:59.766
- What?
- Don't forget you're on a mic.

09:59.849 --> 10:02.769
So? He still need to fucking 'fess up
to doing shit.

10:02.852 --> 10:04.104
Yes, he does.

10:05.063 --> 10:07.482
Whenever the fuck you see him,
you need to talk to him.

10:07.565 --> 10:09.734
- If you see him again, bro.
- You too, bro.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.861
Take your fucking charge.

10:11.986 --> 10:13.905
That's what he needs to do.
Take your charge.

10:14.030 --> 10:16.658
'Cause me being charged with distribution
ain't going to look good.

10:16.741 --> 10:18.493
Yeah, he's gotta take his charge.

10:23.373 --> 10:26.960
At the scene of a crime,
if there are multiple, uh, perps,

10:27.043 --> 10:31.506
we are very careful to keep those inmates
apart in our facility.

10:33.049 --> 10:35.885
We actually are more likely
to get to the facts of the case

10:35.969 --> 10:37.470
if we can keep them separated.

10:44.644 --> 10:47.355
Mom, I need you to bond me out.

10:47.772 --> 10:50.108
<i>- Why, what did you do?</i>
- I did nothing!

10:50.191 --> 10:53.611
He was supposed to drop me off
this morning and we got pulled over.

10:53.695 --> 10:54.904
And he had all of it on him.

10:55.321 --> 10:57.031
- Please, Mom.
<i>- How much is the bail?</i>

10:57.115 --> 10:59.784
- $1500.
<i>- Oh, my God.</i>

10:59.868 --> 11:01.077
Please, Mom. I cannot...

11:01.161 --> 11:02.287
<i>I don't have money.</i>

11:02.370 --> 11:04.372
Ask... Ask Grandma.

11:04.455 --> 11:06.791
<i>Grandma doesn't have $1500 laying around!</i>

11:06.875 --> 11:09.961
Mom, I can't stay here, Mom.
I'm going to lose it, Mom.

11:10.044 --> 11:11.880
I'm... I'm... This is real jail.

11:11.963 --> 11:14.340
This is real jail
and I'm in here for a weapons charge.

11:14.424 --> 11:17.010
<i>I'll ask around, but nobody is
going to give me that much.</i>

11:17.093 --> 11:19.304
Please, Mom.
You have to get me out, Mom.

11:19.387 --> 11:21.639
I cannot stay here. I will not last, Mom.

11:21.723 --> 11:22.599
<i>Oh my God.</i>

11:22.682 --> 11:25.143
Mom, I'm going to diein here
if you don't help me.

11:39.782 --> 11:41.409
I think I've been to jail four times.

11:43.119 --> 11:44.746
This time it's going to be different.

11:46.039 --> 11:49.250
Feels like I've been locked up forever,
way more than 45 days.

11:50.084 --> 11:53.254
Woke up from my nap, I was like,
"Only got a couple of more hours!"

11:53.963 --> 11:56.716
Yeah, I'm very excited. I can't wait.

11:58.218 --> 12:01.221
My <i>oma, </i> she's here visiting from Germany.

12:01.304 --> 12:02.764
<i>Oma</i> means Grandma in German.

12:03.473 --> 12:06.059
I haven't seen her
in, like, six, seven years.

12:06.142 --> 12:07.602
So I'm so excited.

12:07.685 --> 12:10.146
It's going to be so deep. I can't wait.

12:12.815 --> 12:14.817
Your first time getting in trouble?

12:14.901 --> 12:16.319
- You got possession?
- Yeah.

12:17.654 --> 12:19.072
I've been locked up 45 days.

12:19.614 --> 12:22.408
Well, I'm here for violation of probation,
non-reporting.

12:22.992 --> 12:23.993
Petty shit.

12:25.870 --> 12:27.163
When you going home, tomorrow?

12:27.914 --> 12:29.540
In the morning, one o'clock.

12:30.250 --> 12:32.752
- So excited!
- What'll you do when you get home?

12:33.795 --> 12:36.464
- Uh, try not to get high.
- I hear you.

12:37.131 --> 12:39.175
Try to leave the methylenes alone.

12:41.219 --> 12:43.846
<i>I guess you could say I've been an addict
since I was six.</i>

12:45.014 --> 12:46.849
When I was born, my...

12:47.392 --> 12:51.938
my mom was only 15 and she wasn't
really, like, ready to be a parent.

12:52.939 --> 12:55.400
Mom would go to these parties,
make me go with her...

12:56.025 --> 12:59.279
and she would be like,
"Make me a shot! Make me a drink."

12:59.362 --> 13:01.698
I was like the bartender, and...

13:02.699 --> 13:04.617
every time I made them a drink,
I made me a drink.

13:04.701 --> 13:07.287
The first couple of times I was doing it
because I was thirsty.

13:07.829 --> 13:10.665
And then after a while,
like, I was just like...

13:11.332 --> 13:12.292
I liked the buzz.

13:15.211 --> 13:18.506
My mom didn't give a fuck 'cause
she was doing her thing, you know.

13:19.048 --> 13:20.800
Having her little parties and shit.

13:21.467 --> 13:25.722
It made me growing up kind of difficult
'cause I had to be the mom,

13:25.805 --> 13:29.058
and I really didn't get to be the...
the child.

13:49.537 --> 13:50.830
Oh...

13:51.956 --> 13:53.624
And it's all fucked up because...

13:55.543 --> 13:58.546
now I'm not here for my kids
and I bet they feel the same way.

14:19.942 --> 14:23.529
- I'm thirsty.
- Carlos Lopez?

14:24.864 --> 14:26.366
- Brown?
- Okay.

14:28.659 --> 14:30.036
Mr. Brown, come on down, sir.

14:30.578 --> 14:31.913
Do I have a bond?

14:31.996 --> 14:36.584
You've got four felony charges, all
no bond, because you're on probation.

14:36.959 --> 14:38.669
Possession of cocaine,

14:38.753 --> 14:41.756
possession with intent
to distribute marijuana,

14:42.382 --> 14:44.884
possession of a gun
during the commission of a crime,

14:45.510 --> 14:48.471
and possession of a firearm
by a convicted felon.

14:50.848 --> 14:53.309
<i>Now I can't get out of here, no bond.</i>

14:54.143 --> 14:56.020
<i>It's 'cause I'm on probation.</i>

14:56.729 --> 14:59.148
Probation is a whole other field.

15:01.150 --> 15:02.735
They can do whatever they want.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.154
Whether I'm guilty or not.

15:08.241 --> 15:10.410
Sir, you're here on two felony charges.

15:10.910 --> 15:14.205
One is manufacturing, selling,
or distributing marijuana,

15:14.288 --> 15:16.165
possession of a weapon
during a crime.

15:16.249 --> 15:20.044
Your total bond, $12,700.

15:20.128 --> 15:23.214
- I didn't have none of this stuff on me.
- That's up to a judge.

15:24.215 --> 15:26.676
<i>Charging three people for one crime.</i>

15:27.635 --> 15:33.724
<i>My plan for Slim is to get him to confess,
admit to his guilt and sign an affidavit.</i>

15:33.808 --> 15:37.812
I'm getting a lawyer once I get out and
I'm going to fight the case all the way,

15:37.937 --> 15:39.272
and I'm going to win.

15:40.314 --> 15:41.357
Where the boy at?

15:41.816 --> 15:44.152
Slim? You didn't see him in his room?

15:44.235 --> 15:45.945
He's in that last cell.

15:54.620 --> 15:57.748
The phones in the admissions area
are free.

15:57.832 --> 16:02.795
So that allows the inmates to be able to
make those phone calls and bond out.

16:02.920 --> 16:05.256
Because we encourage them
to try to bond out.

16:05.339 --> 16:10.178
We hold that inmate for up to
48 hours. If they're unable to bond out,

16:10.261 --> 16:13.764
we begin to process them
for general population.

16:13.848 --> 16:18.102
Mom, I have to get out. This is
the only night I can bail out, Mom.

16:18.186 --> 16:20.188
This is the only night
or I have to stay here.

16:20.271 --> 16:22.273
<i>You won't. You're innocent.</i>

16:22.356 --> 16:26.027
<i>You were there as just a bystander.
He was dropping you. This gun is his.</i>

16:26.110 --> 16:27.487
I can't snitch on him.

16:28.613 --> 16:33.367
I don't want that guy to hurt me. I don't
want him to come to my house or anything.

16:33.451 --> 16:36.746
Can you... can you call Grandma?

16:37.455 --> 16:39.499
<i>- I did, I just called her.</i>
- What did she say?

16:40.208 --> 16:43.920
<i>Well, she... she said
she doesn't have that money.</i>

16:46.214 --> 16:47.340
Oh, my God.

16:47.423 --> 16:48.591
Oh, my God.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.843
<i>- Alex. Alex.</i>
- What am I gonna do?

16:50.927 --> 16:54.096
- Oh, my God...
<i>- You're gonna be okay.</i>

16:54.180 --> 16:55.431
I don't know, Mom.

16:56.098 --> 16:57.433
I don't know, Mom.

17:04.565 --> 17:08.069
<i>It's just me and my mom. You know,
she's all I got. Just me and my mom.</i>

17:08.152 --> 17:09.694
<i>So we look out for each other.</i>

17:12.240 --> 17:16.243
<i>I'm from the east side of Atlanta, so...
it's not in the best area.</i>

17:16.327 --> 17:17.787
Russom, come on.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.665
<i>When you're in a neighborhood like that,
you go outside</i>

17:20.748 --> 17:23.000
<i>and see folks fighting,
shooting and all that.</i>

17:23.084 --> 17:25.252
That is just what you see.
It's what you know.

17:26.628 --> 17:29.799
I mean, when I was nine years old,
my brother was shot on my doorstep.

17:31.092 --> 17:33.094
Killed on my doorstep, and...

17:33.928 --> 17:34.845
I seen it.

17:34.929 --> 17:38.057
That's... that's what happened,
Eugene was killed.

17:42.853 --> 17:44.522
The more people that you got around you,

17:44.605 --> 17:47.567
more shit, more things can go wrong,
if you feel me?

17:47.650 --> 17:50.236
So I just... don't do that.
I just stay in the house.

17:50.319 --> 17:53.656
I just do my own thing,
but there's only so much you can do.

17:56.617 --> 17:59.996
<i>Obviously, I'm wrong place, wrong time.
That's any time.</i>

18:07.295 --> 18:09.839
Dearest Heavenly Father,
we thank you for this day, Lord.

18:09.922 --> 18:11.382
Watch our friend as she leaves here.

18:11.465 --> 18:13.884
Guide and protect her.
Send your angels to cover around her.

18:13.968 --> 18:16.262
Father, God, in Jesus' name, amen.

18:16.345 --> 18:17.305
Amen.

18:19.515 --> 18:20.850
No crying!

18:20.933 --> 18:23.436
That was beautiful.
That was beautiful.

18:25.146 --> 18:28.190
<i>These girls are amazing. They really
inspire me to really do good.</i>

18:28.649 --> 18:31.819
It's the only thing, you know,
that has kept me wanting to be here.

18:32.737 --> 18:34.697
- She said wrap it up.
- All right.

18:35.364 --> 18:37.116
It's hard. It's real, girl.

18:38.034 --> 18:41.120
Just the experience for these girls
and me leaving them. I don't want to.

18:41.203 --> 18:42.622
