You want to go to rehab
for sure this time?

37:20.488 --> 37:21.322
Mm-hm.

37:23.616 --> 37:24.451
It's just...

37:25.910 --> 37:27.162
...it's just awful.

37:31.040 --> 37:33.376
Is it so hard to get away from it?

37:34.043 --> 37:35.295
Is it...? What...?

37:36.045 --> 37:38.173
How strong is that feeling?

37:39.132 --> 37:39.966
To do it?

37:40.717 --> 37:42.093
Is it strong?

37:46.848 --> 37:49.225
Sometimes your body gonna shut down.

37:49.726 --> 37:51.853
Don't do this to yourself.

37:54.439 --> 37:55.565
And your children.

37:57.817 --> 38:00.361
You want her to get clean too, don't you?

38:01.780 --> 38:02.822
Tell her.

38:03.948 --> 38:05.992
That's all she talks about, is her mama.

38:08.119 --> 38:10.789
We can have a ball,
we can go cruising again.

38:10.872 --> 38:12.665
We can go to Germany, you know.

38:23.009 --> 38:24.177
Oh...

38:28.097 --> 38:29.516
Oh...

38:29.682 --> 38:32.727
You're from a strong family,
you can do this.

38:36.022 --> 38:37.482
You can do this, baby.

38:40.527 --> 38:41.986
You just gotta want to.

38:42.612 --> 38:44.197
You gotta want to do it.

38:46.574 --> 38:47.450
Okay?

38:49.744 --> 38:53.248
If you don't do it for me, do it for
yourself, do it for your children.

39:17.438 --> 39:18.356
Agh...

39:21.609 --> 39:25.780
There was a written affidavit
from Alex that was presented in court...

39:26.364 --> 39:29.409
saying that everything was his,
he claimed responsibility,

39:29.492 --> 39:31.327
and they still didn't let me go home.

39:59.564 --> 40:00.982
This is Christian Masiah.

40:01.691 --> 40:03.693
Martin, this is my 10-year old.

40:05.820 --> 40:08.323
He lives in Stone Mountain
with my brother.

40:08.823 --> 40:10.450
You're in fourth grade? Fifth?

40:10.533 --> 40:12.452
- Going to fifth.
- Going to fifth. Okay.

40:13.411 --> 40:14.537
It's new to me.

40:15.538 --> 40:17.999
<i>It's a new start for me, I know.</i>

40:18.416 --> 40:21.878
<i>The only thing I thrive for now
is the love of my family, you know.</i>

40:23.171 --> 40:24.088
Want an ice cream?

40:24.505 --> 40:25.965
- Yeah, I'll go with you!
- Yes!

40:26.507 --> 40:29.719
It's about time for an ice cream.
I ain't had one in a while.

40:49.530 --> 40:50.657
I was a superstar.

40:52.617 --> 40:54.911
I'm a good person.
I give out good energy.

40:55.578 --> 40:59.832
I should show confidence,
so good energy's going to come back to me.

40:59.958 --> 41:02.460
- That's my lucky dollar. Can...?
- Now.

41:04.629 --> 41:06.547
I hate these stupid ass fucking pigs.

41:08.174 --> 41:10.885
That fuckin' badge don't mean shit!
You don't even have a gun.

41:10.969 --> 41:12.553
You're not a real cop.

41:13.096 --> 41:14.639
Even though what I do is wrong...

41:14.722 --> 41:16.391
These people have a book.

41:16.933 --> 41:18.810
...I do it for the right reasons.
